"{\"uid\": \"cbc.ca-news-canada-british-columbia-olympic-village-elementary-school-1.7165482\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The province announced a long-awaited elementary school is coming to Vancouver's Olympic Village neighbourhood nearly 17 years since a site was first chosen and four years after the B.C.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 69, \"end\": 78, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.390711381843542e-17, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}, {\"begin\": 81, \"end\": 96, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"score\": 0.9530916165659008, \"rank\": 0.04921707695100232, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\"}, {\"begin\": 182, \"end\": 186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.790851928795747e-17, \"text\": \"B.C.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NDP's promise of a fast-tracked process.\", \"from\": 187, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 187, \"end\": 190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Democratic_Party\", \"score\": 0.9999999280771615, \"rank\": 6.349347763228318e-08, \"text\": \"NDP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Democratic_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Democratic_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At a news conference Friday, Education Minister Rachna Singh announced funding of $150 million to build the Olympic Village school, which will welcome 630 students in 2029.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 258, \"end\": 276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Education_minister\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.959426632493865e-26, \"text\": \"Education Minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Education_minister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Education_minister\"}, {\"begin\": 277, \"end\": 289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachna_Singh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rachna Singh\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachna_Singh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachna_Singh\"}, {\"begin\": 337, \"end\": 352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"score\": 0.9530916165659008, \"rank\": 0.04921707695100232, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With so many new people choosing B.C.\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 437, \"end\": 441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.790851928795747e-17, \"text\": \"B.C.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"as their home in recent years, we know that now is not the time to cut back on building schools where they are needed the most,\\\" Singh said.\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The announcement comes following rising demand for school spaces in Vancouver neighbourhoods, especially from families in the Olympic Village and Kitsilano neighbourhoods.\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 652, \"end\": 661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.390711381843542e-17, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}, {\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"score\": 0.9530916165659008, \"rank\": 0.04921707695100232, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\"}, {\"begin\": 730, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kitsilano\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6174058155074414e-19, \"text\": \"Kitsilano\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kitsilano\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kitsilano\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elementary schoolsroutinely hold lotteriesfor scarce kindergarten spots.\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlucky children who do not make the cut end up on wait lists, their families forced to travel to schools in other neighbourhoods that do have space.\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Or families choose to pick up and move elsewhere.\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This neighbourhood really needs a school.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1073, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, like all of central Vancouver really needs more kindergarten spots,\\\" Olympic Village resident Ashlie Corcoran told CBC'sThe Early Edition.\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1221, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1103, \"end\": 1112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.390711381843542e-17, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}, {\"begin\": 1152, \"end\": 1167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"score\": 0.9530916165659008, \"rank\": 0.04921707695100232, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\"}, {\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corcoran_School_of_the_Arts_and_Design\", \"score\": 0.811327834616579, \"rank\": 0.23248017798270534, \"text\": \"Corcoran\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corcoran_School_of_the_Arts_and_Design\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corcoran_School_of_the_Arts_and_Design\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Documents from 2007 show plans for a future school site on Columbia Street, adjacent to Hinge Park, but the site remained untouched for over a decade.\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During the 2020 provincial election campaign, then-premier John Horgan and the B.C.\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.790851928795747e-17, \"text\": \"B.C.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NDP ran on a promise to fast-track the school, citing years of neglect from the B.C.\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1459, \"end\": 1462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Democratic_Party\", \"score\": 0.9999999280771615, \"rank\": 6.349347763228318e-08, \"text\": \"NDP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Democratic_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Democratic_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 1539, \"end\": 1543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.790851928795747e-17, \"text\": \"B.C.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Columbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Liberal party to re-invest in education infrastructure.\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the announcement, Olympic Village parent Aryana Sye expressed optimism about the new school and the opportunities it would create for her young daughter, Chiara.\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1622, \"end\": 1637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"score\": 0.9530916165659008, \"rank\": 0.04921707695100232, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\"}, {\"begin\": 1645, \"end\": 1651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7281652590077226e-17, \"text\": \"Aryana\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariana\"}, {\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erromanga_language\", \"score\": 0.9999998425642058, \"rank\": 1.5050053225028278e-07, \"text\": \"Sye\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erromanga_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erromanga_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1758, \"end\": 1764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chiara_Lubich\", \"score\": 0.9338466485254016, \"rank\": 0.07076063190776623, \"text\": \"Chiara\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chiara_Lubich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chiara_Lubich\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This investment and infrastructure is not just about buildings.\", \"from\": 1767, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's about building the foundation for young families to thrive,\\\" Sye said.\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1907, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Corcoran says the area's current catchment school, Simon Fraser Elementary, is a 25-minute walk away.\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 2010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1966, \"end\": 1972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fraser_River\", \"score\": 0.9304662891712123, \"rank\": 0.07472805094529389, \"text\": \"Fraser\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fraser_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fraser_River\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While she understands budgeting priorities can be challenging for officials, Corcoran says it's been \\\"difficult to get information\\\" about why it took so long to announce a new school.\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2089, \"end\": 2097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corcoran_School_of_the_Arts_and_Design\", \"score\": 0.811327834616579, \"rank\": 0.23248017798270534, \"text\": \"Corcoran\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corcoran_School_of_the_Arts_and_Design\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corcoran_School_of_the_Arts_and_Design\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Without a school in this neighbourhood, there is not an anchor for families \\u2026 and each of those families has to make a choice about whether they are going to relocate when it comes time for school.\\\"\", \"from\": 2197, \"to\": 2396, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She now worries whether further densification will put pressure on the new school when it finally opens.\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Victoria Jung, chair of the Vancouver School Board (VSB), says an Olympic Village school has been a \\\"top priority\\\" for the past decade.\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2504, \"end\": 2512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen_Victoria\", \"score\": 0.9988628052385391, \"rank\": 0.0011371301628770208, \"text\": \"Victoria\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen_Victoria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen_Victoria\"}, {\"begin\": 2513, \"end\": 2517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Jung\", \"score\": 0.9999999970514182, \"rank\": 2.8805429197962086e-09, \"text\": \"Jung\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Jung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Jung\"}, {\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_School_Board\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vancouver School Board\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_School_Board\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver_School_Board\"}, {\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.390711381843542e-17, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}, {\"begin\": 2570, \"end\": 2585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"score\": 0.9530916165659008, \"rank\": 0.04921707695100232, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village_station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Singh says there was \\\"a lot of navigation\\\" behind the scenes to get approvals, given how small the allotted space is and the plan to create a four-storey building.\", \"from\": 2641, \"to\": 2804, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She adds the ministry is in contact with the VSB to ensure new schools and those under construction are able to alleviate enrolment pressures.\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2948, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Singh also announced $15 million in funding to expand the Henry Hudson Elementary school project, which is currently undergoing seismic upgrades, to create space for 145 more students.\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 3134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3008, \"end\": 3020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Hudson\", \"score\": 0.9999999517185654, \"rank\": 4.828141436948943e-08, \"text\": \"Henry Hudson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Hudson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Hudson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Both these investments will help address the enrolment growth that these neighbourhoods are facing,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3136, \"to\": 3247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jung says the much-needed space is a welcome addition to Henry Hudson, as the Kitsilano community has \\\"been impacted by growing density.\\\"\", \"from\": 3249, \"to\": 3386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3249, \"end\": 3253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Jung\", \"score\": 0.9999999970514182, \"rank\": 2.8805429197962086e-09, \"text\": \"Jung\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Jung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Jung\"}, {\"begin\": 3306, \"end\": 3318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Hudson\", \"score\": 0.9999999517185654, \"rank\": 4.828141436948943e-08, \"text\": \"Henry Hudson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Hudson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Hudson\"}, {\"begin\": 3327, \"end\": 3336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kitsilano\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6174058155074414e-19, \"text\": \"Kitsilano\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kitsilano\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kitsilano\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The expansion construction is expected to start in the summer, alongside the ongoing construction of the seismically-safe Henry Hudson Elementary school,\\\" she said, noting the addition will bring the school's capacity to 535 students.\", \"from\": 3388, \"to\": 3623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3511, \"end\": 3523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Hudson\", \"score\": 0.9999999517185654, \"rank\": 4.828141436948943e-08, \"text\": \"Henry Hudson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Hudson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Hudson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The addition, Jung says, will create six classrooms, more resource rooms, expand library space and add a new covered outdoor area.\", \"from\": 3625, \"to\": 3755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3639, \"end\": 3643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Jung\", \"score\": 0.9999999970514182, \"rank\": 2.8805429197962086e-09, \"text\": \"Jung\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Jung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Jung\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Arrthy Thayaparan is a Toronto-based multimedia journalist.\", \"from\": 3759, \"to\": 3818, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's interested in health, climate and community stories.\", \"from\": 3819, \"to\": 3877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She has previously worked at Reuters and CBC Vancouver.\", \"from\": 3878, \"to\": 3933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3907, \"end\": 3914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999991935691083, \"rank\": 8.064316372965732e-07, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 3919, \"end\": 3922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_News\", \"score\": 0.9999976138002514, \"rank\": 2.384804303586466e-06, \"text\": \"CBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_News\"}, {\"begin\": 3923, \"end\": 3932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.390711381843542e-17, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can contact her at arrthy.thayaparan@cbc.ca.\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 3982, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With files from Karin Larsen and The Early Edition  Audience Relations, CBCP.O.\", \"from\": 3984, \"to\": 4063, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Box 500 Station AToronto, ONCanada, M5W 1E6  Toll-free (Canada only):1-866-306-4636  It is a priority for CBC to create products that are accessible to all in Canada including people with visual, hearing, motor and cognitive challenges.\", \"from\": 4064, \"to\": 4300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4170, \"end\": 4173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_News\", \"score\": 0.9999976138002514, \"rank\": 2.384804303586466e-06, \"text\": \"CBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_News\"}, {\"begin\": 4223, \"end\": 4229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.951277941462281e-12, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ca